"title": "6134: coveting, prohibition of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "6134",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Coveting is forbidden by God and can lead to terrible consequences. It occasionally refers to a commendable earnest desiring.</p>\n<h2>Coveting is forbidden by God</h2>\n<h3>In the Ten Commandments</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:17\">EXO 20:17</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:21\">DEU 5:21</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom7:7-Rom7:8\">ROM 7:7–7:8</a></strong> <em>Coveting is provoked by the law that forbids it.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom13:9-Rom13:10\">ROM 13:9–13:10</a></p>\n<h3>Through the prophets</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa5:8\">ISA 5:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa57:17\">ISA 57:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek33:31\">EZK 33:31</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos2:6\">AMO 2:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos5:11-Amos5:12\">AMO 5:11–5:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos8:5-Amos8:6\">AMO 8:5–8:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic2:2\">MIC 2:2</a></p>\n<h3>In Jesus Christ's teaching</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:19-Matt6:21\">MAT 6:19–6:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:15\">LUK 12:15</a></p>\n<h2>Coveting has some terrible consequences</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam11:2-2Sam11:4\">2SA 11:2–11:4</a> <em>adultery</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs21:18-1Kgs21:19\">1KI 21:18–21:19</a> <em>murders</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:1-Matt18:3\">MAT 18:1–18:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:33-Mark9:35\">MRK 9:33–9:35</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:46-Luke9:48\">LUK 9:46–9:48</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:9-1Cor6:10\">1CO 6:9–6:10</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:3-Acts5:10\">ACT 5:3–5:10</a> <em>God's judgment</em></p>\n<h2>Further examples of coveting</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh7:21\">JOS 7:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut7:25\">DEU 7:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh22:20\">JOS 22:20</a> <em>Achan</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam2:12-1Sam2:15\">1SA 2:12–2:15</a> <em>Eli's sons</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam8:3\">1SA 8:3</a> <em>Samuel's sons</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam15:9-1Sam15:10\">1SA 15:9–15:10</a> <em>Saul</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov30:16\">PRO 30:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer6:13\">JER 6:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer8:10\">JER 8:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab2:5\">HAB 2:5</a> <em>Israel's enemies are likened to the grave, always swallowing people and never satisfied</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:13-Acts8:23\">ACT 8:13–8:23</a> <em>Simon the sorcerer</em></p>\n<h2>Believers may pray to be free from coveting</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:36\">PSA 119:36</a></p>\n<h2>Godly people claim not to have coveted</h2>\n<h3>Samuel</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam12:3-1Sam12:5\">1SA 12:3–12:5</a></p>\n<h3>Paul</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:33\">ACT 20:33</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor9:12\">1CO 9:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor7:2\">2CO 7:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor11:9\">2CO 11:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor12:14-2Cor12:18\">2CO 12:14–12:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess2:5\">1TH 2:5</a></p>\n<h2>Coveting as a commendable earnest desiring</h2>\n<p>A desire for the greater spiritual gifts:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:31\">1CO 12:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:1\">1CO 14:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:39\">1CO 14:39</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim3:1\">1TI 3:1</a> <em>a desire to serve in a leadership role in the church</em></p>",
